	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But it's not as necessary now that the DPCM Split technique is known.</div>
<br />The DPCM split is far from ideal. As far as I can tell your method is not scanline-oriented, which means that the split can't be dynamically moved up and down at runtime (meaning it can't be used for skipping the status bar à la Crystalis, for example). And my method, which is scanline-oriented, uses too much CPU time (up to 20% of the 240 visible scanlines for <strong>each</strong> split). I'm trying to cut that time down, but have failed so far.
<br />
<br />Also, I have nothing against giving up the DPCM channel, but I'm sure a lot of people plan to keep using it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


