		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">clueless wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I want to have 8-way background scrolling.  I'm willing to live with scroll artifacts on the edges if I must, but like most people, would prefer to avoid them.</div>
<br />There are a couple of tricks to completely avoid scrolling glitches that do not require mapper IRQs. In my game for example I decided to disable rendering for the first 16 scanlines, which not only hides the glitches but also gives me more time for VRAM updates. In a custom cart the best option would be 4-screen mirroring, of course. A status bar really complicates things though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


