		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">At some point I'm going to make custom mappers for PowerPak to support "swapless" development using the to-be-standard(?) NES&lt;-&gt;PC link cable that blargg has been advocating. I think this should cater to pretty much every need a developer could ask for.</div>
<br />I've got the first version of this working. It's a command line tool to transfer an iNES ROM to NES. It's not very useful for development yet, however, because it always transfers the full ROM, and with mapper data alone taking &gt;40KB it's not fast enough for that. Next I'll start working on only transfering the differences in PRG and CHR and not re-uploading the mapper each time, but that'll require some work on the mappers first.
<br />
<br />Anybody out there who could test it? PowerPak and PC-&gt;NES cable is required.

		

